Class Player

  • java.lang.Object
    • players.Player
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    ComputerPlayer, HumanPlayer

    public abstract class Player
extends java.lang.Object
    A class to keep players in the game. There are different players: human and computer.
    Version:
    1.0
    Author:
    Wouter Bezemer, Wiljan Vinke

        public Player(java.lang.String name,
              Color color1,
              Color color2,
              Board board,
              int numberPlayers)
        Constructs a new Player. If less than 4 Players have been specified, an extra set of Rings will be given with a different Color. The size of the extra set depends on the number of Players.
        Parameters:
        color1 - The Color of the first set of Rings
        color2 - The Color of the second set of Rings
        board - The Board the Player will play on
        numberPlayers: - The number of total Players who will be playing the game
